docs:

#### docsheader ####
text: Add an about page
----
ref: about
#### docstext ####
text: You can use the about page to provide more extensive information about your community.

#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to your [community settings](../#manage) and click **Pages** in the left menu.
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Under **About page** section fill in the text field with your content. Basic formatting is supported.
----
image: pages.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click **Save** button to persist the changes.

#### docsheader ####
text: Add a curation policy page
----
ref: curation-policy
#### docstext ####
text: You can use the curation policy page to announce to other users what are your criteria for accepting submissions to the community.
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to your [community settings](../#manage) and click **Pages** in the left menu.
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Under **Curation policy** section fill in the text field with your content. Basic formatting is supported.
----
image: pages.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click **Save** button to persist the changes.

#### docsheader ####
text: Remove a page
----
ref: remove

#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to your [community settings](../#manage) and click **Pages** in the left menu.
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Clear the text field of the of the page you'd like to remove.
----
image: pages.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click **Save** button to persist the changes.
